Q: incompatible types: inference variable V has incompatible bounds (SSE / Jackson) A: <p>change this line</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>.map(data -&gt; SseFluxUtils.toSseEvent(data, targetJsonView));
</code></pre>
<p>to</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>.map((Object data) -&gt; SseFluxUtils.toSseEvent(data, targetJsonView))
</code></pre>
<p>as your invoke() method returns Flux&lt;T&gt; where T is completely unbound:</p>
<p>java</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>public &lt;T&gt; Flux&lt;T&gt; invoke() {
    return (Flux&lt;T&gt;) getMethod().invoke(...);
}
</code></pre>
